cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.LG

The paper presents a deep learning framework for super-resolution in coherent imaging systems, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory (IT) as it deals with enhancing the space-bandwidth product of coherent imaging systems. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for super-resolution is an artificial intelligence (AI) technique, making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The paper also involves multimedia (MM) as it deals with image data and convolutional neural networks. Finally, the paper involves machine learning (LG) as it uses deep learning techniques.
